results.title: Entrepreneurs
results.description: A down-on-his-luck P.R. man steals a power harness built by three ex-A.I.M. engineers and tries his hand at super-heroics

results.title: Family Ties (The Name of the Rose, Part 1)
results.description: The Kingpin trains his son Richard to be his successor, unaware that Richard is secretly working with the new Rose; an incorrect photo credit puts the lives of Peter Parker and his family in jeopardy

results.title: Three the Hard Way (The Name of the Rose, Part 2)
results.description: The Rose sends the Triad Brothers to eliminate Peter Parker

results.title: The Dark Within (The Name of the Rose, Part 3)
results.description: Richard Fisk breaks the Hobgoblin out of the Tombs and sends him against Spider-Man and Peter Parker; the Demogoblin breaks free from the Hobgoblin's body

results.title: The Best Defense (The Name of the Rose, Part 4)
results.description: A power-mad Richard Fisk dissolves his partnership with the Rose; the Hobgoblin and the Praetorian Guard capture Spider-Man

results.title: The King Makers (The Name of the Rose, Part 5)
results.description: Richard Fisk takes over his father's empire and disposes of his former partner; a new player adopts the identity of the Rose

results.title: A Rose by Any Other Name ... (The Name of the Rose, conclusion)
results.description: Richard Fisk consolidates his position as the new Kingpin of Crime; Spider-Man teams with the Hobgoblin to stop the Blood Rose from killing Fisk

results.title: The Twilight Heroes
results.description: Spider-Man tries to stop Ludlow Grimes from killing the Smithville Thunderbolt, while Peter Parker tries to stop a local reporter from exposing the Thunderbolt's identity

results.title: Prelude:  The Spider's Thread
results.description: Spider-Man's agent (from Amazing Fantasy 15 and Amazing Spider-Man 1) recalls his brief relationship with the wall-crawler

results.title: Sleight of Mind!
results.description: Mysterio, with the unwilling help of Max Schiffman, tries to convince Spider-Man that he never became a superhero

results.title: Making Amends Meet
results.description: When Betty Leeds learns too much of the Foreigner's activities, she is targeted for assassination

results.title: Foreign Affairs
results.description: When Betty Brant Leeds attempts to kill the Foreigner, she runs up against his Death Squad

results.title: The Test (Hobgoblin Reborn, Part One)
results.description: The Foreigner sends the Hobgoblin to assassinate Moon Knight and Nick Katzenberg, then informs Spider-Man of the hits

results.title: Target Two (Hobgoblin Reborn, Part Two)
results.description: Spider-Man and Moon Knight race to find Nick Katzenberg before the Hobgoblin does; meanwhile, the Spider-Doppelganger breaks the Demogoblin out of the Tombs, and Hag and Troll free Venom from a Vault transport vehicle

results.title: Storm Shadows (Spirits of Venom, Part 1)
results.description: Spider-Man and the Hobgoblin are attacked by the Demogoblin and the Spider-Doppelganger; Ghost Rider and John Blaze encounter Venom while searching the New York sewers for the Deathspawn

results.title: Enemies:  A Hate Story (Spirits of Venom, Part 3)
results.description: While the Demogoblin prepares to kill the captive Hobgoblin, Spider-Man, Ghost Rider and Blaze rescue the innocent prisoners of the Deathwatch

results.title: Opening Volley (My Enemy's Enemy ..., Part 1)
results.description: Blood Rose begins an all-out assault on the remnants of the Kingpin's criminal empire; Richard Fisk washes ashore on an (almost) deserted island

results.title: Uneasy Alliances ...  (My Enemy's Enemy ..., Part 2)
results.description: Blood Rose escapes from Spider-Man only to discover that the Foreigner has been hired to kill him

results.title: The Swords Are Drawn  (My Enemy's Enemy ..., Part 3)
results.description: Spider-Man's search for Blood Rose takes him to the Foreigner's HQ, where he encounters the new Enforcers; Richard Fisk steals a power glove and flees the island, forcing Trench to become Nightwatch once again

results.title: The Star Brand
results.description: Ken Connell comes across the Old Man who gives him the Star Brand.  He later battles an alien who wants it.

results.title: Enemies
results.description: An American ex-soldier gains mass powers and uses them to wreak havoc in Russia.  Ken throws him into deep space.

results.title: Celebrity
results.description: Ken gets a new costume and goes public.

results.title: Farewell, Pittsburgh
results.description: Ken and the Old Man fight at a comic book convention, killing thousands.  Ken then tries to rid himself of the star brand, destroying Pittsburgh in the process.  Debbie (now Maddie) finds out that she's pregnant.

results.title: Ghosts
results.description: Ken and Debbie's child is borne, killing her in the process.  He has amazing powers.

results.title: Sins of the Father...
results.description: Roger is turned into a stud by the baby, who confronts Ken in space.

results.title: Family Ties
results.description: A family near the Pitt left by Pittsburgh's remains gets a skin disease and then grows into a blob-like creature.

results.title: Let There Be Life...
results.description: A gross life form emerges from the Pitt and is killed by the baby.

results.title: Giants in the Earth
results.description: A Canadien border guard uses newfound paranormal powers to arrest a paranormal (Leland Sharp) attempting to cross the border.

results.title: Death - Where Is Thy Sting?
results.description: The baby is now a child.  He restores Roger to his normal form, cures Billy, eliminates death on Earth, and gives part of his power to Jacob Burnley.

results.title: The Big Fix
results.description: Jacob Burnley uses the Star Brand power to unsuccessfully restore the city of Pittsburgh to normal.

results.title: We, the People
results.description: Jacob Burnley battles the President of the United States, who is an evil paranormal.  Burnley wins the battle, but is "killed" in the process.  He returns in the alien form at the end of the story.

results.title: Finale
results.description: The star child reveals that he, the old man, and Connell are all the same person.  He attempts to banish the Star Brand power form our universe (somewhat unsuccessfully).

results.title: Taking Charge!
results.description: Ken foils nuclear terrorists, and survives a point blank nuclear explosion in the process.

results.title: Close Encounter
results.description: Some 'students' at Pitt make contact with Ken.  He blows up a mountain on the moon.

results.title: The Fight!
results.description: Ken gets into a struggle with some paranormals.

results.title: Crossing the Line
results.description: Ken arranges for the 'students'  (really middle-eastern spies) to be arrested on guns charges and stages a mild attack on Libya in reprisal for their efforts against him.

results.title: Dead Duck!
results.description: The Old Man shows up again.  He fights Ken in space and seemingly is destroyed once again.

results.title: The Reckoning!
results.description: The Old Man threatens and injures Debbie.  He fights Ken and this time is supposedly killed for good.

results.title: The Brand of a Hero
results.description: Ken meets a sickly kid, Tad Selby, and reveals the star brand's powers to the youth.  He then destroys a massive pile-up of toxic waste dumped by a local company.
